metadata.name: Poem Of Atoms #24
metadata.description:
There is a force in the universe that binds everything together
It's a electronic web that connects everything in a delicate balance. 
Some call it fate. But few know the truth.
They are the lifeblood of our society, and they are what keep us moving forward. We are constantly surrounded by them, and they are always changing. It's not a force, it's an orbit. And the dots are the energy sources.

Made with P5js

metadata.name: BWEEPS  #188
metadata.description:
A minimalist, black-and-white generative profile picture (PFP) created to commemorate one-year anniversary of Bwople project by Gengoya. The artwork is derived from an initial sketch of Bwople which, despite being not the one that was chosen, still managed to captivate interests. The project provides a unique glimpse into an alternate universe in which Bwople could have been represented.

All images are hand-drawn work by Gengoya and composed by Vector Recite using PureSpider's fxhash-pfp maker tool.

To download the full size image on fx(hash):
- Click "open" below the image
- Left click on the image, a "Download image" button will appear on the bottom right.
- Click the "Download image" button.

metadata.name: La Invernada #25
metadata.description:
This project is about my mother's lifestyle. Her work is breeding and herding goats, cows and horses.
She lives a cyclical life marked by two major stages during her livestock year: "La Veranada" and "La Invernada". My last work was about "La Veranada", this work is about "La Invernada", I hope you enjoy it.
Time in the life of a criancero is cyclical. Everything comes and goes, and comes back and comes back. Nature, so present, so in connection with the man and woman who inhabit it, marks the times perhaps like no other place.
 The succession of the seasons, the weather, the buds and "La Invernada", the sowing, the pastures, the harvest and the snows.
"La Invernada" is the place during what we could call the long winter, that is, from April to November.
"La Invernada" is down in the plains, in the pampas, in accessible places, where it is easy to supply forage to the goats that calve between October and November.
The "Criancero" rides a horse every day and, accompanied by his dogs, goes to "watch" the goats. They distinguish them in the distance. Every day is the same and different at the same time. Caring for, watching over and keeping the goats healthy and safe.
"El puesto" is their home. In the stall they use the water from the river, which they draw with a water pump, for their hygiene. Water for consumption is brought in jerry cans from "Vertientes", located about 10 km away.
 The hens roam freely throughout the day, when night comes some go to sleep in the "gallinero" and others simply sleep on small plants.
As you can see, life here is simple, solitary and with a lot of work.
I want to thank all those who have taken the trouble to read the story. I hope you liked it.
You can find real photos and videos of "La Invernada" on my twitter profile.

Features:
10 Color Palettes.
10 types of Animal pen.
Various types of chickens.
14 types of herbs.
10 types of flowerpot.
4 types of trees.
7 types of rivers.
The barn has 4 sizes.
The moon has a very varied range of x and y positions.
6% chance of getting snowy weather in the piece.


Press "S" in live mode to save the 2600 x 3000 image.
Note that the algorithm may take some time to run.
Created by Fernando. NFT 2.0 license.

metadata.name: A study in Entanglement #24
metadata.description:
"A study in Entanglement" starts with a blank canvas which branches explore. Some branches finish up early, while others fall off the canvas, continuing to infinity. Who knows where they will end up?

-

This is my first generative project, while I am beginning with creative coding. I will be releasing the code for my study series, with the intention of sharing what I am learning.

Enjoy!

https://github.com/gitpancake/entanglement

metadata.name: Microreactors/A Box of Chocolates #235
metadata.description:
Objects drifting in a cell generate beautiful and complex patterns. They look like "Concentration fluctuations caused by thermal convection in microreactors". It also evokes Forrest Gump's famous line "Life is like a box of chocolates".

There is a phase difference between adjacent cells, generating similar but different patterns.

Each of them can be seen as a parallel world of life.

In addition, the observer can interfere with the pattern by clicking and dragging the mouse.
